--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
EXCLUSIONS — packages deliberately NOT bundled into the OSS distribution
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

`litellm-enterprise` (BerriAI Enterprise License — commercial):
  Status: NOT installed by the production deploy script.
  Why noted: this package may appear in a developer's local venv if pip
   resolved an older path; ClawNex's production install path (`pip install
   litellm[proxy]==1.83.0`) does not pull it because none of `litellm`,
   `litellm[proxy]`, or `httpx` declare it as a dependency. Operators who
   independently `pip install litellm-enterprise` are agreeing to BerriAI's
   commercial Enterprise Terms separately.
  Action: do not import or call into `litellm_enterprise.*` from anywhere
   in ClawNex source. Verified empty: `grep -r "litellm_enterprise" src/
   litellm/ scripts/` returns no matches.

`litellm-proxy-extras` (dual-licensed — MIT for the core, BerriAI Enterprise
for any `enterprise/` subdirectory):
  Status: installed in the production venv as a litellm-proxy transitive.
  Scope of use: ClawNex consumes only the migration.sql files which live
   in the MIT-licensed portion. No code is imported from any `enterprise/`
   subdirectory of this package.

